This paper deals with propositional logic and uncertainty modeling, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The use of probability measures also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA). Finally, the paper's focus on axiomatization and complexity analysis suggests a possible connection to programming languages (cs.PL).
